                                   "apps/backend/app/routers/"
                               ],
                     "step":  2,
                     "description":  "Explore the backend structure: config.py for settings, database.py for data layer, llm.py for AI integration. The routers define HTTP endpoints while services contain business logic.",
                     "title":  "Backend Architecture"
                 },
                 {
                     "files":  [
                                   "apps/backend/app/models.py",
                                   "apps/backend/app/database.py"
                               ],
                     "step":  3,
                     "description":  "Understand the SQLite database with SQLAlchemy. The Database facade returns plain dicts, not ORM objects. Key tables: resumes, jobs, improvements, applications, api_keys (encrypted).",
                     "title":  "Database Layer"
                 },
                 {
                     "files":  [
                                   "apps/backend/app/llm.py",
                                   "docs/agent/llm-integration.md"
                               ],
                     "step":  4,
                     "description":  "LiteLLM provides multi-provider support (OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama, etc.). The llm.py module handles JSON mode, retries, and provider-specific configurations.",
                     "title":  "LLM Integration"
                 },
                 {
                     "files":  [
                                   "apps/backend/app/services/",
                                   "apps/backend/app/prompts/"
                               ],
                     "step":  5,
                     "description":  "Services contain business logic: parser.py (document parsing), improver.py (resume tailoring), refiner.py (keyword injection), cover_letter.py (cover letter generation). Prompts define LLM templates.",
